Not doing MDS? That doesn’t mean your clinical journey has to end.
Here are 5 high-paying, hands-on career paths for BDS graduates who still want to stay inside the clinic 👇

1️⃣ Implantologist
Implants are booming. With proper hands-on training and good planning skills (like CBCT & case selection), you can earn ₹15K–₹50K per case.
💡 Tip: Start assisting senior implantologists and invest in a short certified course.

2️⃣ Cosmetic Dentist
Smile designing, veneers, teeth whitening — these are premium services that patients are actively looking for.
Cosmetic dentistry works best in urban areas and private setups. Combine it with photography & digital tools to stand out.

3️⃣ Endodontics (Without MDS)
Single-visit RCTs using rotary + rubber dam are in high demand across clinics.
With repetition, your speed, confidence, and earnings all increase.
💡 Tip: Focus on mastering access, canal prep, and sealing.

4️⃣ Clinical Trainer / Mentor
If you’re good at explaining and love guiding juniors, you can teach suturing, extraction, basic endo, etc., via hands-on training.
Workshops, webinars, or even 1:1 mentorship = clinical + educational impact.

5️⃣ International Prep with Clinical Work
If you’re preparing for ORE, GDC, or ADC, you can continue working clinically alongside it.
This gives you income now + opens international doors later. Smartest dual strategy.

Medical Coding for Dentists 🦷💻
If clinic life isn’t for you or you’re exploring non-clinical options after BDS, this is something worth looking into.
✅ Remote jobs
✅ Decent pay
✅ Short training
✅ Uses your dental knowledge

Want a list of best training platforms + free beginner resources?
👇
Comment ‘CODING’ and I’ll send it to you personally!

#dentistry #bdscareer #medicalcoding #nonclinicaldentist #dentaljobs

1. Medical Content Writer
	•Write articles for dental blogs, health websites, or ed-tech platforms
	•Tools: Google Docs, Grammarly, ChatGPT
	•5K–₹40K/month (depending on clients)
2. Online Dentistry Tutor
	•Teach dental subjects to juniors or NEET MDS aspirants
	•Platforms: Zoom, Google Meet, Superprof, Classplus
	•500–₹1000/hour | Create paid courses later
3. Teleconsultant (Teledentistry)
	•Provide basic dental consultation remotely
	•Apps: Practo, Lybrate, MyDentalPlan
	•10K–₹25K/month side income
4. Resume/CV & SOP Consultant for Dental Students
	•Help others build career-focused resumes, especially for MDS, UK, abroad
	•Tools: Canva, Notion, Google Docs
	•500–₹1500
5. Medical Coding (Remote Dental/Healthcare Coder)
	•Translate clinical data into alphanumeric codes for insurance & billing
	•Tools: ICD-10, CPT, Excel, company-provided software
• 15K–₹35K/month (India-based jobs); ₹50K+ if US clients or AAPC-certified
6. Digital Product Seller
	•Sell career guides, patient education sheets, planner templates
	•Tools: Gumroad, Notion, Canva
	•Passive income ₹299–₹999 per sale
7. UI/UX Design (Healthcare or EdTech Design Specialization)
	•Design user interfaces for apps, websites, tools — especially in health, wellness, or ed-tech sectors
	•Tools: Figma, Adobe XD, Canva, Notion
•20K–₹60K/month as freelancer | ₹1L+/month with experience
8. Freelance Research Assistant / Journal Reviewer
	•Assist with literature reviews, case reports, abstracts
	•Platforms: Fiverr, Upwork, direct networking
	•1000–₹3000 per project
9. Customer Success Agent for Dental Startups
	•Handle user queries for dental SaaS tools, apps, e-com platforms
	•Tools: Slack, Freshdesk, WhatsApp CRM
	•8K–₹20K/month | Flexible shifts
10. Affiliate Marketer for Dental Products
	•Promote tools, scrubs, instruments, courses with your link
	•Tools: Instagram, WhatsApp, affiliate dashboards
	•Earn per sale (₹100–₹5000 depending on product)

🎓 You don’t need to do everything. You just need to choose right.

Start with clarity, not confusion. 
📌  Save it — this one reel can literally save you ₹30K and 6 months

🩶 To anyone who’s cried in the changing room, doubted themselves mid-residency, or felt invisible after doing their best — you’re not alone. OMFS breaks you, but it also builds you. Stronger. Sharper. Softer in the right ways.

And if I had to choose again? I’d still walk into that OT.
Again. And again. And again.

✨To every branch — whether you’re perfecting a smile, managing the unspoken pain, guiding recovery, or making invisible differences every single day — you are doing something extraordinary. This journey isn’t easy for any of us. And whatever you’re doing — is enough. And it matters.
